Interface RemoteVehicleServiceInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
RemoteVehicleServiceInterface.Stub
public interface RemoteVehicleServiceInterface
extends android.os.IInterface

The AIDL interface for a RemoteVehicleService running in a separate process. This interface is used to bind to an AIDL interface in order to interact with a centralized RemoteVehicleService that is reading data from a vehicle, trace file or other source. Applications should use the in-process VehicleService, as that builds the proper Measurement types before returning - the data at this level is very loosely typed in order to slip through the limited AIDL interface.
